/**
 * Outstanding.gs — Claim Outstanding Mirroring (Enterprise Mode, ES5-safe)
 * =============================================================================
 * Mirrors hourly from "Overview Claim" → "Claim Outstanding", with:
 * - Region routing via "Store Region" sheet (Partner Name → Region sheet), merged-header safe
 * - Special routing: Partner Name Digimap/Digiplus → sheet "Digi"
 * - Adds "PIC" column (derived from raw Last Status + Service Center)
 * - Preserves manual columns (configured) by Claim Number (rich text safe)
 * - Translates raw "Last Status" → friendly text in destination
 * - Queue + batch processing + retry w/ exponential backoff + circuit breaker
 * - Idempotent per hour (prevents double enqueue in same hour)
 *
 * Operational notes:
 * - Recommended: bind this script to the DEST spreadsheet ("Claim Outstanding")
 * - Setup: run install() once, then runNow() to test
 *
 * [Unverified] Assumptions:
 * - Source headers are on row 1; data starts row 2 for all source sheets.
 * - Destination schema is exactly EXPECTED_COLUMNS + "PIC".
 * - "Store Region" layout: row1 = region name, row2 = subheaders incl "Partner Name",
 *   row3+ = data.
 */

